\u0101n r\u00f3ng xi\u0101ng l\u00e1n}}, [[Jawi script|Jawi]]: \u062a\u0646\u062c\u0648\u06a0 \u06a4\u0646\u062f\u0646 ), is the largest town on the island [[Belitung]] in the [[Indonesia]]n province of [[Bangka-Belitung]], [[Indonesia]]. Tanjungpandan is the capital of the [[Belitung Regency]] comprising one of the five [[Districts of Indonesia|districts]] (''kecamatan'').\n\n==Demographics==\n\nThe majority of the people in Tanjungpandan are [[Indonesian Chinese|Hakka Chinese]] and [[Malays (ethnic group)|Malay]]. The religions of the Malays are [[Muslem]] and the Chinese are [[Buddhist]], [[Catholic]] and [[Protestant]].\n\n==Transportation==\nIt has [[H.A.S. Hanandjoeddin International Airport]] which serves links to Jakarta, Pangkalpinang and Palembang ( via Pangkalpinang ).\n\nAs of June 2011, the port has 6 shipping terminals:\n* International Terminal\n* Dry Bulk Terminal\n* Liquid Bulk Terminal\n* Roll-on Roll-off Ship Terminal, including Cargo Ship\n* Domestic Terminal\n* Container Terminal\n\n==Hotel==\n\n*Grand Hatika Hotel\n\n*Grand orion Hotel\n\n*Meigah Hotel\n\n*Arnava Hotel Belitung\n\n*Demuon Hotel\n\n*Maxone Hotel\n\n==Tourist attraction==\n\n*Tanjung Pendam Beach\n\n*Rumah adat Belitung\n\n*Satam roundabout\n\n*Kampong Belitong timpo duluk\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Tanjung Pandan}}\n\n<!--{{coord|2|45|S|107|45|E|source:frwiki_region:ID_type:city|display=title}}-->\n\n* [http://korindo-network-travel.com/tanjung-pandan/bangka-belitung-tour.htm Bangka Belitung - Tanjung Pandan Activity]\n\n[[Category:Populated places in the Bangka-Belitung Islands|Bangka]]\n[[Category:Regency seats of the Bangka Belitung Islands]]\n\n\n{{BangkaBelitung-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{unreferenced|date=December 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2014}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                    = Tanjungpandan \n| native_name             = \n| native_name_lang        = <!-- ISO 639-2 code e.g. \"fr\" for French. If more than one, use {{lang}} 