eroa || [[Frankton, Waikato|Frankton]] \u2013 [[Morrinsville]] \u2013 [[Paeroa]] \u2013 [[Waihi]] \u2013 [[Tauranga]] \u2013 [[Taneatua]] || Closed Paeroa to Apata, September 1978. Waikino to Waihi reopened 8 November 1980 by [[Goldfields Railway]]. Hawkens Junction to Taneatua became Taneatua Branch. \n|-\n| '''[[Cambridge Branch]]''' || Ruakura \u2013 Hautapu \u2013 [[Cambridge, New Zealand|Cambridge]] || Freight only. Closed Hautapu \u2013 Cambridge 1999\n|-\n| [[Glen Afton Branch]] || || Closed, partially remains as the Bush Tramway Club's Pukemiro Line. Remainder became Rotowaro Branch\n|-\n|[[Kimihia railway station#Kimihia colliery branch|Kimihia Branch]]||  || Coal only\n|-\n| '''[[Glen Afton Branch|Rotowaro Branch]]''' ||\n| Coal only\n|-\n| [[Thames Branch|Thames Branch/'''Waitoa Branch''']] || [[Morrinsville]] \u2013 [[Waitoa]] \u2013 [[Paeroa]] \u2013 [[Thames, New Zealand|Thames]] || Morrinsville to Paeroa part of East Coast Main Trunk, 1928 to 1978. Freight only. Closed Waitoa \u2013 Thames 1991. Mothballed Morrinsville to Waitoa, reopened 2004 as Waitoa Branch.\n|-\n| [[Glen Massey Branch|Wilton Collieries Line]]||[[Ng\u0101ruaw\u0101hia]]|| Closed, 1958 (Line owned by NZ Mines Dept, operated by NZR after 1940)\n|}\n\n====Bay of Plenty====\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Name !! Route !! Usage\n|-\n| '''[[Kinleith Branch]]''' || Waharoa  \u2013  [[Kinleith Mill]] || Freight only \n|-\n| '''[[Mount Maunganui Branch]]''' || || Freight only\n|-\n| '''Murupara Branch''' || || Freight only\n|-\n| [[Rotorua Branch]] || [[Putaruru]] \u2013 [[Rotorua]]/Koutu || Leased to a Private Operator, 2010\n|-\n| [[Taneatua Branch]] || || Mothballed 2003\n|-\n| [[Whakatane Board Mills Line]] || Awakeri \u2013 Whakatane mill || Closed 2003\n|}\n\n====Gisborne \u2013 Hawke's Bay====\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Name !! Route !! Usage\n|-\n| '''[[Ahuriri Branch|Napier Port Branch/Ahuriri Branch]]''' || || Freight only\n|-\n| [[Moutohora Branch]] || [[Gisborne, New Zealand